<p>

<b>Hilarie Ross Prange</b> (n√©e <b>Burton</b>; born <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../844/15844.xml">
July 1</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../756/34756.xml">
1982</link>) is an <body wordnetid="107965085" confidence="0.8">
<social_group wordnetid="107950920" confidence="0.8">
<political_orientation wordnetid="106212839" confidence="0.8">
<colony wordnetid="108374049" confidence="0.8">
<state wordnetid="108168978" confidence="0.8">
<political_unit wordnetid="108359949" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<democracy wordnetid="106217103" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../750/3434750.xml">
American</link></democracy>
</group>
</political_unit>
</state>
</colony>
</political_orientation>
</social_group>
</body>
 actress. She is perhaps best known for her portrayal of <fictional_character wordnetid="109587565" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../729/2151729.xml">
Peyton Sawyer</link></fictional_character>
 on <network wordnetid="108434259" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../118/3831118.xml">
The CW Television Network</link></network>
 (previously <network wordnetid="108434259" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../240/178240.xml">
The WB Network</link></network>
) television series <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../957/999957.xml">
One Tree Hill</link></series>
</it>. She hosted <channel wordnetid="106259898" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../856/18856.xml">
MTV</link></channel>
's <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../260/200260.xml">
Total Request Live</link></series>
</it>, which led to a starring role as the character.</p>
<p>

Burton rose to stardom with leading roles in the films <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../175/10002175.xml">
Our Very Own</link></movie>
</it>, <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../730/9468730.xml">
Solstice</link></it> and <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../467/11395467.xml">
The List</link></movie>
</it>.</p>

